hese problems, but requires $\\epsilon_e > 1 (k = 2)$, spherical outflow, and\n$\\epsilon_B < 10^{-9}$. Conclusions. In light of the extreme microphysical\nparameters required by the energy-injection model, we favour a jet-break\nscenario where $\\nu_m < \\nu_{sa}$ to explain the observations. This scenario\ngives physically meaningful microphysical parameters, and it also naturally\nexplains the reported detection of linear and circular polarisation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 25 Mar 2015 19:53:28 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 9 Apr 2015 14:01:26 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 2 May 2016 12:30:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-05-03"}
